<br>
Talendor - naggy on crack. roughly a 4k fire based dot, and a fear. the fear is easy to resist at 60 with decent MR (he didnt fear me once), but your lower levels will get pillaged. this is maintank fight, so keep some clerics, and just do some damage.<br>
<br>
Wuoshi - a velious dragon, but still 32k. Has an aoe fear and aoe poison (disease maybe?) 3 second stun. i played a cleric and a monk for the fight. Monk, at 60, didnt get feared once, but the stun landed way too often. the cleric at 53 ate almost all of both aoes. the only strategy i can say is get a 60 tank, and have EVERY healer setup on him/her (NO CHEALS, you wont get them off between stuns, use divine light), and just spam hoping atleast one of you resists the stun. the fear is weak and fairly easy to resist, and even if you dont, just run back and fight. the stun is your issue.<br>
<br>
Severillous - another 32k, this one was dead before i could even figure out what he was doing. same aoes as wuoshi, easier to resist. a joke of a dragon, just watch the stuns.<br>
<br>
Ragefire - not exactly a raid for loot mob, has a 300ish dmg aoe and no fear, thats about all. 32k again, a joke.<br>
<br>
Eldrig the old - correct me if im wrong, but he is just some skyfire named, so most likely soloable by any capable druid.<br>
<br>
and of course:<br>
Gorenaire - the only dragon yet to fall to me. The aoe 750dmg+slow is crucial. your best bet is to try to dodge the first, and go full offensive before she fires again. her fear is IMO the roughest of the kunark dragons. most importantly, she cheals. this can be dealt with in two ways, in my mind. we had a wizard kite her while enchanters ran around and sieved her. this worked, except for the fact that we lost 4 enchanters. or, just manaburn her at 40-50%.<br>
<br>
that goes for all kunark dragons, a nice touch of manaburn and they are a joke.<br>
<br>
